I’m so tired but just cannot fall back to sleep.

Also, I don’t think I can take anymore naps. I’m a little tired of watching TV. I’ve loved FT’ing with my niece & nephew, sister, & friends. I’m obsessed with the HouseParty app and overwhelmed by the IG Live craze. If you have any suggestions on how to remain sane, let me know.

So, I don't think I love almond milk. I've been making smoothies with it for the past 4ish weeks but I couldn't smell or taste anything. And now that my smell and taste have returned, I think this might be the end of almond milk for me.

I tested positive for COVID19 the 3rd week of April. I’m now fully COVID-free. 

It’s good to be able to smell & taste again. I had a long shedding period - it lingered even as I wasn’t spreading it.

Thanks to all who provided care & for the ease of setting up this house visit. https://t.co/SUyYPyWq8R
@rianalynn taste/smell is still slowly returning. taste is better than smell at the moment.

I just tested positive for COVID-19. I lost my sense of taste about a week ago — a mild symptom, the doctor said. Quarantine has now turned into isolation. Luckily, taste is beginning to come back. The doc expects me to recover fully, told me to call if I have any chest pains.

I’m also reminded that there’s so much about COVID-19 that even the doctors still don’t know. 

The anti-body test results were good, too.

After multiple tests, I’m happy this is over. & shout-out to @CityMD for having such a smooth & easy process. #StayHome
